The paper deals with the problem of local alignment in biosequence databases, which is a common topic in computer science research related to data structures (cs.DS) and databases (cs.DB). The paper proposes an efficient algorithm for evaluating local-alignment searches, which involves designing and implementing new techniques for filtering and reusing score calculations, which could fall under the category of computational engineering (cs.CE). The paper also involves mathematical analysis and experimental study, which could be related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
